docs.lead_paragraph: Who knew trade wars were so complicated? A United States trade agency on Friday surprisingly rejected calls by Boeing and the Trump administration to impose duties on Bombardier’s CSeries jet. It shifts the regional-airplane dogfight back to the marketplace, where it belongs, raising the pressure on Boeing to seal a tricky merger with Embraer.

headline.main: Bombardier’s Win Adds Pressure on Boeing to Strike Embraer Deal
